Reasoning: The paper proposes a new analysis method for phenomena on networks, which involves categorizing nodes based on local statistics and using visualization techniques to understand the behavior of networks. This falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses primarily on network analysis and visualization, we consider cs.SI and cs.SD (Systems and Control) to be the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.NI, cs.DS, and cs.LG.
